com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Interface DownloadItem


  • public interface DownloadItem
    Provides different information such as file URL, its mime type, percent complete, received bytes etc. Also it allows registering the DownloadListener to receive download update events for this particular download item.

    • Method Detail

      • addDownloadListener

        void addDownloadListener(DownloadListener listener)
        Adds the specified download listener to receive download update events from this download instance.

        If listener listener is null, no exception is thrown and no action is performed.

        Parameters:
        listener - the download update listener.

      • removeDownloadListener

        void removeDownloadListener(DownloadListener listener)
        Removes the specified download update listener so that it no longer receives download update events from this download instance.
        Parameters:
        listener - the download update listener.

      • getDownloadListeners

        java.util.List<DownloadListener> getDownloadListeners()
        Returns a list of all the download listeners registered on this download item.
        Returns:
        all of this item's DownloadListeners or an empty list if no download listeners are currently registered.

      • getURL

        java.lang.String getURL()
        Returns URL of this download.
        Returns:
        the URL of this download.

      • getBrowser

        Browser getBrowser()
        Returns the browser instance that initiated this download or null if this instance is already disposed.
        Returns:
        the browser instance that initiated this download or null if this instance is already disposed.

      • isPaused

        boolean isPaused()
        Indicates whether this download is paused. Use this method in the DownloadListener.onDownloadUpdated(com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.events.DownloadEvent) event to find out whether download is paused or not.
        Returns:
        TRUE when this download is paused.

      • isCanceled

        boolean isCanceled()
        Indicates whether this download is canceled. Use this method in the DownloadListener.onDownloadUpdated(com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.events.DownloadEvent) event to find out whether download is canceled or not.
        Returns:
        TRUE when this download is canceled.

      • isCompleted

        boolean isCompleted()
        Indicates whether this download is completed. Use this method in the DownloadListener.onDownloadUpdated(com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.events.DownloadEvent) event to find out whether download is completed or not. When download is canceled this method also returns true. Use isCanceled() method to find out whether download is canceled or not.
        Returns:
        TRUE when this download is completed or canceled.

      • getPercentComplete

        int getPercentComplete()
        Returns rough percent complete. -1 means we don't know it, because we didn't receive a total size.
        Returns:

      • getTotalBytes

        Returns the total size of a file in bytes.

      • getReceivedBytes

        long getReceivedBytes()

      • setDestinationFile

        void setDestinationFile(java.io.File destinationFile)
        Modifies the destination file. You can modify the destination file only in the DownloadHandler.allowDownload(DownloadItem) method.
        Parameters:
        destinationFile - new destination file.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when destinationFile is null.

      • pause

        void pause()
        Pauses this download. Will have no effect when the download is already paused.

      • resume

        void resume()
        Resumes this download. Will have no effect when the download is not paused.

      • cancel

        void cancel()
        Cancels this download. Will have no effect when the download is already cancelled.
